description: Demolition of existing waste transfer station and re-development of the site to provide a residential development comprising of three blocks ranging from 5 -11 storeys in height to provide 218 residential units (class C3) with associated landscaping.This application is a DEPARTURE APPLICATION: The proposed development is a departure from its designation as a safeguarded waste site under the Lambeth Local Plan (2015).This application is accompanied by an Environmental Statement (ES) which is available for inspection online with the planning application documents. Electronic copies of the Environmental Statement may be viewed at https://planning.lambeth.gov.uk/online-applications/ using the application reference 20/01822/EIAFUL.This application is linked with the planning application reference: 20/01066/EIAFUL for the development proposed at: Land Off Windsor Grove, Adjoining Railway At West Norwood, London.
